23/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- One person was injured and the windows of several buildings were blown out when two bombs exploded simultaneously in the Macedonian capital Sunday (22 June) afternoon.
Interior ministry spokeswoman Mirjana Kontevska told reporters the explosive devices had been planted in garbage containers, one near the Mavrovka shopping centre and the other near Macedonian Telecom.
She added that anti-terrorist units are investigating.
(AP - 23/06/03;
A1 TV, SRNA - 22/06/03)
